<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-03-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="361" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Bigelow</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 77.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-03-23"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 23, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received your despatch of March 6,
                            No. 44.</p>
                        <p>Unemployed politicians can often raise vehement disputes upon mere
                            surmises or accidents, as they can sometimes prohibit all debate upon
                            the most questionable measures.</p>
                        <pb facs="0470" n="388" xml:id="pg_388"/>
                        <p>The French government can very well understand that our delay in filling
                            the legation at Paris was involuntary, because that government has
                            really found the appointment of a minister here was a duty attended by
                            some embarrassment.</p>
                        <p>I thank you for the information you gave me concerning the negotiations
                            of Maximilian at Rome for a concordat.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>